etymology:
From Ottoman Turkish یوممق (yummak, “to shut, close (the eye, the fist)”), from Proto-Turkic *yum- (“to close (eyes, mouth)”).
Compare Proto-Mongolic *ǯimüji- (“to close eyes; mouth”), (Buryat жэмыхэ (žemyxe, “to compress, squeeze, purse one's mouth”)) and Proto-Tungusic *ńim- (“to close eyes”) (Evenki нимӈи (ņimŋi, “to close, to shut eyes”)).
